Delta Air Lines Inc said it beganconstruction to expand its passenger terminal facilities atDallas/Fort Worth International Airport.    Adding a new nine-gate terminal that will be connected toDelta's existing terminal by an underground tunnel will costabout 20 mln dlrs, a Delta spokesman said.    The carrier will have a total of 32 gates, up from thecurrent 23, when the terminal is completed in late 1988.    With the new "satellite" terminal, Delta will be able toexpand to more than 300 daily flights at the airport, up fromabout 200 currently, it said. Reuter&#3;